Introduction¶

Dataset description¶

This dataset collects information from 100k medical appointments in Brazil and is focused on the question of whether or not patients show up for their appointment. A number of characteristics about the patient are included in each row. The data set is available for download here For this data set will wil be investigating what factors affect the turning up of a patient for his or her appointment. There are many factors given in this data set that we will analyze they are listed in the columns below.

Column Description¶

  • PatientId - Identification of a patient (A patientID can appear multiple times thus we use it to knoow how many times a patient visited the hospital
  • AppointmentID -Identification of each appointment
  • Gender - Male or Female (represented as M and F)
  • Scheduled day - The day of the actual appointment, when they have to visit the doctor.
  • Appointment day - The day someone called or registered the appointment, this is before appointment of course.
  • Age - How old is the patient.
  • Neighbourhood - Where the appointment takes place, i.e the area where the hospital/health centre is
  • Scholarship - It indicates whether or not the patient is enrolled in Brasilian welfare program Bolsa Famlia. The value 0 represents False and 1 represents True. True in the sense that the patient is a beneficiary of the scholrship scheme and False the patient is not.
  • Hipertension -Shows if the patient is hipertensive or not 0 representing hypertensive and 1,not hypertensive.
  • Diabetes - Shows if the patient is Diabetic or not 0 representing Diabetic and 1,not Diabetic.
  • Alcoholism - Shows if the patient has alcholic problems or not 0 representing alcoholic and 1,not alcoholic.
  • Handicap - Shows if the patient is handicapped or not, and how many handicap conditions.
  • SMS_received - If the patient received a reminder sms or not
  • No-show - If the person shows up or not.No if the patient showed up to their appointment, and Yes if they did not show up.

Question(s) for analysis¶

The main questions we are asking in this projects are the factors that determine if a patient shows up for his appointment, but we will dabble in a few others as to understand how these factors correlate with each other.

  1. Which gender tend to show up for their appointment?
  2. Do patients with the same scheduled day and apointment day show up or not and the proportion of patients with the same scheduled day and appointment day who show up?
  3. What are the effects of the scholarship program regarding show up or not?
  4. Does the neighbourhood of the hospital affect a patient showing up or not?
  5. Do age/age group affect show or no show?

These questions will be treated in no particular order and more questions and answer may be poised as we get more insights into the data.

In [27]:
#create binning function
def binning(col, cut_points, labels=None):
    #Define min and max values
    minimum = col.min()
    maximum = col.max()
    
    #create list by adding min and max to cut_points
    break_points = [minimum] + cut_points + [maximum]
    
    #Binning using cut function of pandas
    colBin = pd.cut(col,bins=break_points,labels=labels,include_lowest=True)
    return colBin

#Binning age:
#dividing age into age groups using the pandas cut function
cut_points=[20, 40, 60, 80, 100]
labels=['0 - 20 years', '21 - 40 years', '41 - 60 years','61 - 80 years', '81- 100 years','100-120 years']
df["Age_group"] = binning(df["Age"], cut_points, labels)
print(pd.value_counts(df["Age_group"], sort=False))

Conclusions¶

From this data set, the following conclusions can be made after performing an exploratory data analysis on it:
First well discuss about Age
The age column is positively skewed with a median of 39 and a mean age of 39 as well.It has a range of (0-115).We also have a few outliers about 4 patients who are 115 years old. A large number of missed appoint ment were from the 21-40 group this may be as a result of commitments at that particular age in life.Looking futher in the age column we see that most appointments where scheduled for babies(Age 0-1).Age is a significant factor for predicting show and no show.

Gender
There are more females than males that visit the hospital in general but looking at the proportion of show to no show, It can be said that Gender is not an important factor for predicting show and no show because Mles and females have almost the same proportion of show to No show

Neighbourhood
The rate of show to no show are average for almost all neighbourhoods, Although JARDIM CAMBURI has the highest number of patients but this factor has a lot of limitations as well. Therefore it isnt significant for predicting show nd no show.

Scholarship
A small proportion of the patients are on scholarships.Following the link to the Bolsa Famlia,scholarship beneficiary are generally indigent people and checking the trend of Show to No show, Most patients that are on scholarships, tend to show up for their appointments.I feel that scholarship is a significant fator for predicting show and no show.

Correlations
Looking through age and gender, we see that more females than males tend to visit the hospital
Looking at hipertension and age group, we see that people age 41 to 60 are more hipertensive than the others.It may be due to that age patients are more susceptible to high blood pressure.
Looking through Scholarship and age group,The scholarship beneficiaries are more of age 0-40 counting for 70% of the beneficiaries.This may be due to other factors you'll find in this link

Limitations

  1. This data set is limited to a particular country and the trends may be diffrent in another country.
  2. More variables could have been added to the data set like income level of the patient and distance of the patients home to the hospital. These would have helped a lot in predicting show and no show.
